This paper is primarily focused on wireless networking and communication, which falls under the category of Network and Internet Architecture (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the use of software-defined networking (SDN) and its implementation in Bluetooth Low Energy (BLE) mesh networks, which could fall under Information Theory (cs.IT) and Learning (cs.LG) categories. The paper also discusses the need for reliability and real-time network slicing, which could fall under Systems and Control (cs.SY) and Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) categories.
